{
  "texts": [
    "Our aim was to identify & nominate potential carcinogens in literature not curated by existing IARC monograph evidence or belonging to our training data.",
    "Incidentally, False Positives (FP) represented one fifth of our results for EC entities.",
    "Out of these roughly one third were variants of G1 & G2A our noise reduction methods failed to recognize.",
    "Roughly 45% of FP were hypernymy descriptions of entities consisting of broad terms like 'organic extract' and 'soluble particle'.",
    "The remaining FP were incorrectly classified entities."
  ]
}